FBIS4-3876 "drchi080_c_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-080 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 Central Eurasia Li Peng, Nazarbayev Sign Border Treaty in Almaty Li Peng, Nazarbayev Sign Border Treaty in Almaty OW2604093994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0902 GMT 26 Apr 94 OW2604093994 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Almaty, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and Kazakhstan President N.A. Nazarbayev signed a border agreement between the two countries here today. After the signing ceremony, Li called the agreement "a historic document," which defines the over-1,700-kilometer-long border between the two countries in a legal form. This, he said, would serve to boost the development of the existing bilateral relations of friendship. Nazarbayev said the agreement symbolizes a long-term good- neighborly relationship between the two countries. He expected the Sino-Kazakhstan border to be one of peace and friendship. Also signed were an agreement on China providing loans to Kazakhstan, notes to be exchanged on China presenting a batch of materials to Kazakhstan, and a summary of talks on developing international railway transportation between the Chinese Ministry of Railways and Kazakhstan's Ministry of Communications.
